OL,7,F"He knew who we were. He still
OL,8,Fcontinued on his forward momentum as I
OL,9,Fhad my weapon up, pointing at his
OL,10,Fhead," he recalled.
OL,12,F"I remember the surveillance officer
OL,13,Fthen in full body contact with him,
OL,14,Fand apparently what he was trying to
OL,15,Fdo was pin his hands so that he
OL,16,Fcouldn't detonate.
OL,18,F"I'm expecting an explosion at any
OL,19,Fmoment, he's gonna blow. We're gonna
OL,20,Fdie. But that's the nub of it.
