OL,7,FSir Tony Blair, who was prime minister
OL,8,Fat the time, recalled he was in a
OL,9,Fbilateral meeting with the Chinese
OL,10,Fpresident when he received news of the
OL,11,F7/7 bombings.
OL,13,F"I got handed a piece of paper saying
OL,14,Fthere'd been a series of incidents on
OL,15,Fthe London Underground," he said.
OL,17,F"At that time I didn't have any more
OL,18,Finformation about it. The moment you
OL,19,Fget passed a note like that, you
OL,20,Fexpect the worst."
